    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-01-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-01-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="598"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/2388: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Commissioner in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-01-12T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1924—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. With reference to the telegram number 1, January 7, noon, from American
                    Minister, Santo Domingo, the Department desires your views regarding the
                    possible effect of bond issue on political situation in view of approaching
                    elections. This of course does not refer to obligations of Power Company
                    contract. Reply by cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
